This paper is about automatic post-editing (APE) in natural language processing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method that uses neural networks to model the copying mechanism for APE, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses experiments on datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the datasets include image data.
